02V\u00ab 1033\u00ab\nFOREIGN MARKETS.\nLQNDON. Feb. 7 (/Pi.\u2014Price movements\nwere mixed in the stock market today,\nwith the general trend lower. Home\nrails closed firm on higher dividend an\nnouncements and the gilt-edged group held\nsteady. Trans-Atlantic securities were\nfirm throughout the day and in some\ncases finished with gains of 1 to 2 points.\nBrazilian and German bonds were un\nsettled at lower prices and oils and\nmining shares moved irregularly. Indus\ntrials were generally lower.\nPARIS.\u2014Banking shares closed firm in\nfan otherwise weak stock market today,\nlank of France issue gaining 115 francs,\nnternational securities were mixed, with\nSuez Canal moving up 140 francs and\nRoyal Dutch declining 65 francs. Rentes\nlost 5 to 20 centimes.\nU. S. TREASURY POSITION.\n'Reported by Smith, Barney Co.'\nRate\u2014Maturity. Bid. Offer\n3 Mar. IS. '3R 1013-32 1015-32\n2> June lft. \u202238 101 17-32 101 10-32\n2'\"i Sept. lft. '38 101 27-32 101 20-32\n1 Vi'Dec. lft. '38 101 3-32 101 5-32\nIVj Mar. lft. \u201930 101 13-32 101 15-32\n214 June lft, 30 _ 102 1.3-32 102 lft-.\",-'\n1\u20194 Sept. lft. 30 _ 101 14-32 101 10-32\nIV* Dec. lft. '30 101 15-32 101 17-32\nIs* Mar. lft. '40 loi 27-32 101 o0-3\u201d\n1 \u2018i June 15. 40 _ 101 20-32 101 \u2022>\u2022\u2019..(\u20227\n1'; Dec 15. 4o lot 18-32 101 20-32\nl\u2019.-j Mar. 15. 41 _ l\"l 15-32 101 17-32\n13\u00ab June lft. '41 1014-32 1010-32\n1'* Dec. lft. '41 100 25-32 100 27-32\nl3/\u00ab Mar. 15. '42 102 0-32 102 8-32\nS\u00a3Dt' ,15' \u20194- 103 8-33 103 10-32\n154 Dec. 15, '42 102 6-32 102 8-32\n\nNEW YORK BAR SILVER.\nf NEW YORK, Feb 7 (\u00a3>).\u2014Bar silver,\n44%, unchanged.\nJ\nNEW YORK CURB MARKET\n(By private wire direct to The Star.)\nStock and Sales\u2014\nDividend Rate Add 00 High Low Close\nAero Sup A 1.50 5 15 15 15\nAero Sup B.1214k 3 3 3 3\nAir Devices 11 1 1\nAir Invest _ 1 1'4 1'4 H4\nAla Gt Sou (3a) .100s 404 40(4 40(4\nAllied Inti Inv 5 *4 4\nAil\u2019d Intlnv pf 1e 500a 9