resge\nCo. and subsidiaries reported today\nfor 1937 net profit of $10,712,513. equal\nto $1 94 a share of common stock, and\ncompared with $11,042,139, or $1.97 a\nshare, in 1936. Company operates a\nnational chain of stores selling a gen\neral line of low-priced merchandise.\nJ. J. Newberry Co.\nSales of J. J. Newberry Co. in Janu\nary totaled $2,656,065, a decrease of\n3.5 per cent from $2,752,591 in Janu\nary, 1936. it was reported today. Com\npany operates a Nation-wide chain\nof variety stores.\nEdison Bros Stores.\nJanuary sales of Edison Bras. Stores\namounted to $1,183,617. a gain of 13.6\nper cent over $1,042,067 in the com\nparable 1937 month. Company dis\ntributes shoes in a national chain of\nretail stores.\nWestern Auto Supply.\nWestern Auto Supply Co. reported\n86.60 PER 81,000\nMONTHLY\nPAYMENTS\nINTEREST\nat 5%\nWill enable you to own\nyour home outright in\n191,/2 years and eliminate\nneedless worry about re\nnewals and additional\nfees.\nMortgage Loan Correspondents\nW\nInvestors\u2019 Syndicate\nJanuary sales of $1,906,000, an in\ncrease of 6.3 per cent over $1,793,000\nin January, 1937. Company distributes\nauto supplies and sporting goods in\nthe South, Southwest and Midwest.\nLane Bryant Co.\nJanuary sales of Lane Bryant Co.\namounted to $961,012, a decrease of\n7 5 per cent under $1,039,373 in the\nlike 1937 month. The company dis\ntributes women\u2019s and children's\nclothing and shoes in the East and\nMiddle West,\nSpiegel, Inc.\nSpiegel, Inr., Chicago mail order\nhouse, placed January sales at $1\n720 410, a decrease of 6.5 per cent\nfrom $1,840,562 in the comparable\n1937 month.\n\nU. S. TREASURY NOTES.\nNEW YORK. F\u00b0b. 7 4\u2019 -Prices quoted\nIn dolla-s and thirty-seconds:\nApprox.\nPet. Month Year, Bid A^krd. yield.\n:i Mar,. 19 is io]-:s 101.5\n27b June. 19:1s lol-lx 101-20\n2'2 Sept., ]9.'(M lnl-2* lol-uo\n1!\u00bb Dec.. )9iS lol-:; 101-5\nI'a Mar.. 19 19 1111-1:1 101-15 .19\nJune. 19119 _ 101-1:1 101-15 79\nIS Sept. 19119 101-